reviewText:
Another winner with my girls.  It's about Bratz Babyz and they are super!!
They've watched it multiple times.  You think it would get old after so many times...but it will end and they want to watch it again.

The Bratz get computer animated in this adventure film. After their sister accidentally gives the Bratz super powers, the girls must adapt to their new hero personalities. But as soon as they get used to the change, aliens return to earth and rob them of their powers.
Scary for a 6 year old. Baby aliens with monster faces.
Very cute
Felt it was very boring for my grandaughter and she did not care for it either. Characters were actually annoying.

My Granddaughter and I are extremely happy the price was right ,and every one was so helpful in getting the movies to us even though they were sent to the wrong address and I did not have to pay anymore.
Thanks
The Bratz are terrible, but for some reason my daughter wants to watch them.  I will be steering her towards other more appropriate shows.
This is one of the worst movies ever. We will not be watching another again. This is not good for kids.

Don't waste your time (or your kids). This was just the worst cartoon I have ever had to sit with my daughter and watch. The animation was extremely terrible, as if a high schooler did it. Actually, I think a high schooler would have done better!
Written very poorly. I don't know who writes the dialogue for this but it's awful. I guess this is where creators who aren't good enough for Disney end up.
Vapid and painful, a true torture to watch, but the kids liked it. Turn it on and leave the room.
It nice for my grand child to find cartoon  or shows that are on TV. She really like this show so please continue to put good show  on prime! That the the reason I keep prime for to watch movie.
Horrible... just watch the first 30 seconds and see for yourself.  Need to figure out parental guides settings so none of these moves will show up

My goddaughter found it educational and it kept her attention.
Better than some of the foolishiness on TV kids watch.
I as a grandmother don't understand the fascination with this movie, but it kept our granddaughters entertained so I will say it is a keeper.

My five and four year-old cousins could not get their eyes of this show. The valley girl personality of the characters were a bit much and what was up with the silky hair (lol smh)?But the show is for kids so I rated it accordingly.

Don't waste your time.  The babies are decked out in hooker hair and makeup, and while I'm not easily offended, the babies' outfits/hair made me a little uncomfortable and not really what I want my daughter watching.  They look cute on the cover, but the movie itself looks nothing like that. The animation is really bad, cheesy and cheap.  I wish I could give 0 stars.
I loved it so much like i can't believe hat this is the only one that i like didn't see. I wish that I would've seen it sooner
My girls downloaded this and sem to like it! I have not played it yet but they like it a lot
I don't usually consider myself a prudish person, but this was ridiculously terrible.  These "babies" dress like street-walkers and there was not one ounce of content that could redeem this movie.
Ugly movie My grandchild picked it. I am really disappointed with it. The coiors and story represent  an adult theme.
My little girl loves this movie. She watched it at least five times. She asked to watch it by name several times. Since then, she acquired two Bratz Dolls.

I thought it was a cute movie for little kids.  Nothing great, but my granddaughter loved it.  She may want to watch it again, but it's not like the Disney or Pixar movies by any means.  It's just a cute cartoon movie.
it is so awesome my kids LOVE IT!they watch it so much since they are kids right? ~blanca cortes :)

Their attitudes, dress, and well all of it really is not something I would let my 7 year old watch again. There's really not much else to say, if you value what your child watches and realize it affects their thinking then this isn't the show for you.
I have not watched this show but my 6 yr old daughter has watched it many times.  So I am guessing for the age group it is a good movie.

If I could give this 0 stars, I would.  We love the Bratz movies, but this one is just awful.  The animation is terrible and very cheap looking and the story is just dumb.  Don't waste your money or your time....bad, bad movie.
My granddaughters absolutely love this movie. It is now one of their favorites.  They love the Bratz collection of DVDs.

The children absolutely loved this movie and it kept them thoroughly focused and entertained. Great gift idea for your children or other children. Those who enjoy playing with Bratz Babyz will certainly enjoy having this collection with them as well.
I purchased this item for my granddaughter and she enjoyed the movie very much. Not only did we receive the DVD but we also received a free viewing of the entire movie on the computer.
This is cute like the babyz always are!!!! Cloe, Yasmin, Sasha and Jade are the cutest babyz ever!!!!!
Cute enough. My 2 year old enjoys it though it doesn't keep her captivated all the way through. There are dry parts she drifts away from but otherwise, not bad. I bought mine at Target for 7.50.
Good condition happy with movie
I wish my child could un-watch it, but it is too late.  Very violent ending.  Ugly show in so many ways.
Dasha was very pleased!
I cannot stand the Bratz.  I have no idea why anyone thought this was a good show to create for children.
great movie for the kids
great
My kids really enjoyed this!!
My four year old loved this
GOOD
